Transnet's multi-billion rand locomotive deals will be back under scrutiny when the state capture inquiry continues this morning. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Transnet's multi-billion rand locomotive deals will be back under scrutiny when the state capture inquiry continues on Thursday. Transnet Strategy Manager Francis Callard will be testifying for the second time. The inquiry is expected to then shift focus back to the Guptas' wedding party landing at Waterkloof Air Force Base. READ: Waterkloof scandal: Koloane 'ashamed' of implicating Zuma Also on the stand for the second time will be Thabo Ntshisi. He was stationed in the control room at the base when flight clearance requests came from former Chief of State Protocol Bruce Koloane.